The paper deals with signature codes, which are a type of error-correcting codes used in information theory. The paper specifically focuses on signature codes for weighted binary adder channels and multimedia fingerprinting, which are both topics related to information theory and coding. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses collusion-resistant multimedia fingerprinting, which falls under the sub-category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper uses graph theory and constructions, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also mentions two-level signature codes, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
